1
00:00:00,500 --> 00:00:01,400
<i> You used the money.</i>

2
00:00:01,600 --> 00:00:03,267
<i>I thought of it.
The money is all there.</i>

3
00:00:03,433 --> 00:00:06,067
<i>I can't bear saving my grandma
through wrong means.</i>

4
00:00:06,233 --> 00:00:07,467
<i> Let's earn some money today.</i>

5
00:00:07,600 --> 00:00:08,800
<i> Aah!</i>

6
00:00:08,933 --> 00:00:10,733
[SHRIEKS]

7
00:00:10,833 --> 00:00:12,567
[MOTORCYCLE ENGINE REVVING]

8
00:00:12,733 --> 00:00:15,200
<i>My goodness! You almost
broke my earring.</i>

9
00:00:15,300 --> 00:00:17,067
<i>- Why do you have this?!
- I saw it--</i>

10
00:00:17,233 --> 00:00:18,233
<i> This is ours!</i>

11
00:00:18,533 --> 00:00:21,133
<i>If that belongs to them,
does  that mean they were there?</i>

12
00:00:21,267 --> 00:00:23,967
<i>I don't know, but I think we
should tell the cops about this.</i>

13
00:00:24,100 --> 00:00:27,267
<i> I know about the affair, Mom!</i>

14
00:00:28,967 --> 00:00:32,300
<i>Were you there
when Dad died?</i>

15
00:00:36,833 --> 00:00:39,067
Are you accusing me?

16
00:00:40,133 --> 00:00:42,467
[SOBBING]

17
00:00:42,600 --> 00:00:44,500
I don't know, Mom.

18
00:00:49,033 --> 00:00:51,300
[SIGHS SHARPLY]

19
00:00:52,667 --> 00:00:54,667
All I know is that...

20
00:00:55,700 --> 00:00:57,567
you lied.

21
00:00:59,300 --> 00:01:03,933
You have been lying
for a long time.

22
00:01:04,033 --> 00:01:06,333
You're a liar!

23
00:01:07,033 --> 00:01:08,833
No, dear.

24
00:01:09,033 --> 00:01:10,700
Please.

25
00:01:10,833 --> 00:01:13,367
Jade, listen to me.

26
00:01:13,500 --> 00:01:14,767
Please.

27
00:01:14,900 --> 00:01:16,367
I'm tired.

28
00:01:16,533 --> 00:01:19,700
I'm sick and tired
of your lies!

29
00:01:20,733 --> 00:01:22,167
Dear, please listen to me.

30
00:01:22,300 --> 00:01:24,200
Jade, please.

31
00:01:25,900 --> 00:01:27,333
Jade, Mom, what's going on?

32
00:01:27,467 --> 00:01:28,933
[JADE] Listen to you?

33
00:01:29,067 --> 00:01:33,867
- [MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]
- [JADE SOBBING]

34
00:01:34,000 --> 00:01:37,633
Are you going to tell everyone
here the whole truth?

35
00:01:43,933 --> 00:01:46,500
[JADE] Okay, fine.

36
00:01:46,600 --> 00:01:49,900
Fine, Mom.
Let's get the truth out.

37
00:01:50,067 --> 00:01:51,500
What do you mean?

38
00:01:52,733 --> 00:01:53,700
What truth?

39
00:01:54,733 --> 00:01:55,833
Come on, Mom.

40
00:01:58,100 --> 00:01:59,133
Tell them.

41
00:01:59,267 --> 00:02:06,333
[UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]

42
00:02:07,433 --> 00:02:11,567
What were you doing at the
place where Dad died?

43
00:02:15,967 --> 00:02:22,733
[UNSETTLING MUSIC CONTINUES]

44
00:02:28,300 --> 00:02:35,367
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]

45
00:03:31,133 --> 00:03:34,967
[JADE BREATHES SHARPLY]

46
00:03:35,100 --> 00:03:38,800
Why are you suddenly
quiet, huh, Mom?

47
00:03:38,933 --> 00:03:44,300
[UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]

48
00:03:44,433 --> 00:03:48,633
Okay, okay. Then let me tell you
what I think.

49
00:03:51,333 --> 00:03:57,433
[UNSETTLING MUSIC CONTINUES]

50
00:03:57,567 --> 00:04:00,200
Half of this earring
was found

51
00:04:00,367 --> 00:04:02,633
where Dad died.

52
00:04:04,967 --> 00:04:08,333
This belongs to Mom.
Dad gave it to her.

53
00:04:10,200 --> 00:04:12,300
Jade, what are you trying
to say?

54
00:04:12,400 --> 00:04:16,200
Mom was there, and she kept
it from us all this time.

55
00:04:16,333 --> 00:04:22,167
[UNSETTLING MUSIC CONTINUES]

56
00:04:22,300 --> 00:04:23,967
Are you accusing Mom...

57
00:04:25,233 --> 00:04:27,100
- that she knows something--
- Stop it.

58
00:04:27,233 --> 00:04:28,300
Jade.

59
00:04:29,167 --> 00:04:31,733
Enough with those thoughts.

60
00:04:31,900 --> 00:04:34,167
Aren't you getting tired
of all this mess?

61
00:04:34,267 --> 00:04:35,567
[JADE SOBS]

62
00:04:39,033 --> 00:04:41,033
[SOBBING]

63
00:04:46,067 --> 00:04:48,800
It's not just that, Leon.

64
00:04:48,933 --> 00:04:53,067
While I was looking for the
other half of that earring,

65
00:04:53,233 --> 00:04:56,167
I found out that Mom was
going to leave us

66
00:04:56,267 --> 00:04:58,567
before Dad died.

67
00:05:01,767 --> 00:05:03,433
No.

68
00:05:03,567 --> 00:05:05,000
That's not true.

69
00:05:06,100 --> 00:05:07,767
Mom.

70
00:05:07,933 --> 00:05:09,100
Tell us it's not true.

71
00:05:12,033 --> 00:05:13,100
Mom?

72
00:05:14,200 --> 00:05:18,767
[UNSETTLING MUSIC CONTINUES]

73
00:05:19,767 --> 00:05:21,267
No.

74
00:05:21,400 --> 00:05:23,500
We can't report that
to the cops.

75
00:05:23,633 --> 00:05:24,833
Why?

76
00:05:24,967 --> 00:05:26,933
Because we'll look dumb
if we report this

77
00:05:27,100 --> 00:05:29,000
without enough
information.

78
00:05:29,133 --> 00:05:31,833
We don't even know
who owns it.

79
00:05:31,967 --> 00:05:34,667
All we have are theories.

80
00:05:34,833 --> 00:05:37,633
Well, even if your suspicions
are right,

81
00:05:37,800 --> 00:05:39,967
I don't have the
earring anymore.

82
00:05:40,100 --> 00:05:44,433
But that earring will open a new
lead in Papa's case.

83
00:05:44,567 --> 00:05:47,133
Let's just forget it.
It'll only cause trouble.

84
00:05:49,833 --> 00:05:51,267
Suit yourselves.

85
00:05:51,400 --> 00:05:52,900
I already made my point.

86
00:06:00,233 --> 00:06:01,800
[INHALES SHARPLY]

87
00:06:01,967 --> 00:06:02,967
[JADE] Come on, Mom.

88
00:06:04,167 --> 00:06:05,367
Tell them.

89
00:06:08,100 --> 00:06:09,433
That's true.

90
00:06:10,833 --> 00:06:11,567
[LUNA] What?

91
00:06:11,700 --> 00:06:18,733
[UNEASY MUSIC PLAYING]

92
00:06:20,867 --> 00:06:22,567
Why, Mom?

93
00:06:26,033 --> 00:06:27,067
[SOBS]

94
00:06:31,367 --> 00:06:34,400
Come on, Mom. Tell them.

95
00:06:35,967 --> 00:06:37,600
What is it exactly?

96
00:06:39,333 --> 00:06:41,600
[BREATHES SHARPLY]

97
00:06:42,900 --> 00:06:47,033
That she and Uncle Michael
had an affair.

98
00:06:48,033 --> 00:06:54,867
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

99
00:07:00,500 --> 00:07:04,600
And maybe that was the reason
he and Dad killed each other.

100
00:07:05,333 --> 00:07:12,167
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

101
00:07:20,333 --> 00:07:27,133
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

102
00:07:30,867 --> 00:07:32,200
Well, Mom?

103
00:07:34,233 --> 00:07:36,333
Are you trying to come up
with an excuse again?

104
00:07:37,667 --> 00:07:40,967
Why don't we just
tell them everything, Mom?

105
00:07:41,533 --> 00:07:43,067
The earring.

106
00:07:43,200 --> 00:07:44,067
The affair.

107
00:07:44,233 --> 00:07:46,800
The plane ticket.
The approval for residency!

108
00:07:46,933 --> 00:07:48,033
What the heck, Jade?!

109
00:07:49,700 --> 00:07:52,000
[EXHALES SHARPLY]
Come on, Mom.

110
00:07:52,100 --> 00:07:53,100
Tell them!

111
00:07:53,567 --> 00:07:55,767
Tell them, Mom, please!

112
00:07:57,933 --> 00:08:03,333
Y-Your Uncle Mike and I
didn't have an affair.

113
00:08:03,467 --> 00:08:05,500
You are mistaken.

114
00:08:05,633 --> 00:08:08,000
[SOBS] But, Mom, I saw you!

115
00:08:08,767 --> 00:08:12,167
I saw you when I was
just a kid! I saw you!

116
00:08:12,267 --> 00:08:15,900
Why don't you just tell
the truth?!

117
00:08:16,033 --> 00:08:17,567
[SOBS]

118
00:08:17,700 --> 00:08:23,667
[MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]

119
00:08:23,800 --> 00:08:25,067
[SOBS]

120
00:08:33,300 --> 00:08:35,033
I'm sorry...

121
00:08:36,333 --> 00:08:39,867
Maybe... maybe I had feelings
for him.

122
00:08:40,500 --> 00:08:43,600
Maybe I... I needed a man.

123
00:08:43,733 --> 00:08:45,533
'Cause I was miserable.

124
00:08:45,667 --> 00:08:49,200
Your dad and I,
we were miserable.

125
00:08:52,233 --> 00:08:56,533
Your dad and I
had fallen out of love.

126
00:08:58,833 --> 00:09:00,633
The ticket's real.

127
00:09:00,767 --> 00:09:05,433
[MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

128
00:09:05,600 --> 00:09:08,400
Yes, I wanted to go. Alone.

129
00:09:08,500 --> 00:09:10,400
Just like I've always wanted.

130
00:09:12,200 --> 00:09:13,500
And maybe...

131
00:09:15,800 --> 00:09:19,233
Maybe I'm a bad mother.

132
00:09:21,100 --> 00:09:22,267
But...

133
00:09:22,433 --> 00:09:29,233
[MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

134
00:09:32,133 --> 00:09:34,267
But if you want me to confess

135
00:09:34,400 --> 00:09:37,633
that I was the reason
they killed each other,

136
00:09:37,800 --> 00:09:39,533
I can't do that.

137
00:09:39,667 --> 00:09:43,200
If you want me to
tell you that I don't love you,

138
00:09:43,333 --> 00:09:46,500
it's not true, because I...
[SOBS]

139
00:09:46,633 --> 00:09:49,167
I love you so much.

140
00:09:50,500 --> 00:09:52,533
I love you so much.

141
00:09:52,667 --> 00:09:59,467
[MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

142
00:10:01,833 --> 00:10:03,533
[FRIDA] I love you so much.

143
00:10:04,900 --> 00:10:11,833
[FRIDA SOBBING]

144
00:10:13,600 --> 00:10:14,533
But, yes.

145
00:10:15,567 --> 00:10:16,833
[EXHALES DEEPLY]

146
00:10:18,833 --> 00:10:21,133
[BREATHES DEEPLY]

147
00:10:22,400 --> 00:10:24,167
I was there

148
00:10:24,333 --> 00:10:27,800
the day your dad and Mike
got into a fight.

149
00:10:27,900 --> 00:10:29,633
[BREATHES DEEPLY]

150
00:10:29,767 --> 00:10:32,633
- I told you about this before.
- The night before he died,

151
00:10:32,733 --> 00:10:34,367
Fred and I fought.

152
00:10:34,500 --> 00:10:38,133
I told him I wanted to leave,
hence the ticket.

153
00:10:38,267 --> 00:10:41,933
<i>- It's because of Mike, huh?
- He thought I wanted to do so</i>

154
00:10:42,067 --> 00:10:43,067
- because of Mike.
<i> - No!</i>

155
00:10:43,200 --> 00:10:45,533
<i>- Mike has nothing to do...
- Oh, come on!</i>

156
00:10:45,700 --> 00:10:48,367
<i>...with what I want to do
with my life!</i>

157
00:10:49,033 --> 00:10:50,367
[FRIDA] I knew Fred was furious.

158
00:10:50,533 --> 00:10:54,600
So when I saw Mike
pick up your father that day,

159
00:10:54,733 --> 00:10:56,367
I followed them.

160
00:10:58,633 --> 00:11:00,533
<i> Careful, ma'am.</i>

161
00:11:03,767 --> 00:11:05,700
[FRIDA] I asked Roi to drive.

162
00:11:05,867 --> 00:11:07,500
We followed Mike's truck.

163
00:11:08,100 --> 00:11:11,100
<i>Roi, hurry! We need to
catch up to them!</i>

164
00:11:11,633 --> 00:11:12,767
<i> Yes, ma'am.</i>

165
00:11:12,900 --> 00:11:19,467
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

166
00:11:31,000 --> 00:11:32,300
<i> Where did they go?</i>

167
00:11:35,233 --> 00:11:36,633
<i> Drive faster, Roi!</i>

168
00:11:37,600 --> 00:11:38,700
<i> Yes, ma'am.</i>

169
00:11:44,267 --> 00:11:47,500
[ROI] Ma'am, it's a dead end.

170
00:11:47,633 --> 00:11:49,733
<i> Ma'am! Wait, ma'am!</i>

171
00:11:49,833 --> 00:11:50,900
<i> Fred!</i>

172
00:11:51,033 --> 00:11:52,633
<i>- Ma'am!
- Fred!</i>

173
00:11:52,767 --> 00:11:53,800
[GASPS]

174
00:11:53,933 --> 00:11:55,500
<i>- Fred!
- Ma'am!</i>

175
00:11:55,633 --> 00:11:57,667
<i> Roi, find Fred.</i>

176
00:11:57,800 --> 00:12:00,133
<i>Ma'am, just go to the hotel.
I'll go find Sir Fred.</i>

177
00:12:00,267 --> 00:12:02,300
<i>Your children
are waiting for you.</i>

178
00:12:02,433 --> 00:12:05,333
<i>Promise me, Roi, that you'll
take Fred and Mike back.</i>

179
00:12:05,467 --> 00:12:09,167
[FRIDA PANTING]

180
00:12:10,167 --> 00:12:12,300
That's the truth, kids.

181
00:12:13,433 --> 00:12:16,000
Why didn't you tell the police
about this, Ma?

182
00:12:17,033 --> 00:12:19,467
I'm not as strong
as you think I am.

183
00:12:21,133 --> 00:12:23,867
And I'm worried about you.

184
00:12:24,000 --> 00:12:26,800
I don't want you
to think of me differently.

185
00:12:26,967 --> 00:12:33,700
[EMOTIONAL MUSIC PLAYING]

186
00:12:39,733 --> 00:12:42,167
[SNIFFLES] I'm sorry.

187
00:12:45,233 --> 00:12:48,767
I'm sorry that I was
the reason they fought.

188
00:12:51,533 --> 00:12:56,067
I'm sorry that I'm the reason
your daddy is gone now.

189
00:12:58,267 --> 00:13:00,867
[SIGHS SHARPLY]

190
00:13:01,000 --> 00:13:07,700
[EMOTIONAL MUSIC CONTINUES]

191
00:13:15,867 --> 00:13:17,333
[SNIFFLES]

192
00:13:19,867 --> 00:13:23,033
[SNIFFLES, SOBS]

193
00:13:43,700 --> 00:13:45,900
Mom's resting in her room.

194
00:13:45,900 --> 00:13:47,100
Then, I'll leave.

195
00:13:47,100 --> 00:13:48,233
You stay there.

196
00:13:49,767 --> 00:13:51,100
Do Martin and his brothers
know about it?

197
00:13:54,133 --> 00:13:55,200
It's Kiko.

198
00:13:58,133 --> 00:13:59,933
He was the one
who found the earring.

199
00:14:01,333 --> 00:14:03,933
We shouldn't let this
reach the police.

200
00:14:03,933 --> 00:14:10,367
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

201
00:14:10,967 --> 00:14:12,133
Are you still not okay?

202
00:14:14,433 --> 00:14:15,400
[SCOFFS]

203
00:14:16,167 --> 00:14:17,400
That's the problem with you.

204
00:14:18,933 --> 00:14:20,300
You are such a Daddy's girl.

205
00:14:21,000 --> 00:14:22,133
What about your mother?

206
00:14:22,133 --> 00:14:24,067
You want me to stand by her?!

207
00:14:25,467 --> 00:14:27,000
Seriously?

208
00:14:27,000 --> 00:14:29,233
You're so quick to believe her.

209
00:14:29,267 --> 00:14:31,500
Why can't you understand

210
00:14:31,500 --> 00:14:33,500
that she's protecting
Uncle Mike?

211
00:14:36,033 --> 00:14:37,333
You have to see this.

212
00:14:40,167 --> 00:14:41,167
What is this?

213
00:14:44,200 --> 00:14:45,500
Is this Mrs. Almazan?

214
00:14:46,200 --> 00:14:48,133
That was recorded from
a car's dashcam.

215
00:14:48,833 --> 00:14:51,767
On the day Michael Fernandez
and Federico Almazan died.

216
00:14:52,367 --> 00:14:54,467
500 meters away
from the location.

217
00:14:54,467 --> 00:15:01,033
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

218
00:15:01,033 --> 00:15:02,533
[JUSTIN] What are you
trying to imply?

219
00:15:02,567 --> 00:15:05,033
Mom had something to do
with Dad's death?

220
00:15:06,200 --> 00:15:07,867
Jade, do you even
hear yourself, huh?!

221
00:15:08,233 --> 00:15:09,800
You want your mother
to go to jail?!

222
00:15:09,800 --> 00:15:10,900
I just want the truth!

223
00:15:10,900 --> 00:15:12,033
[LUNA] Jade, come on!

224
00:15:13,400 --> 00:15:14,800
What truth do you want?!

225
00:15:17,300 --> 00:15:19,400
Do you want Mom to say
that she killed Dad

226
00:15:19,400 --> 00:15:20,533
- for you to stop?!
- [LEON] That's enough!

227
00:15:22,233 --> 00:15:23,367
[THUDS]

228
00:15:25,900 --> 00:15:27,067
I believe

229
00:15:27,067 --> 00:15:29,467
that Mom and Uncle Mike
don't have a relationship.

230
00:15:30,167 --> 00:15:32,867
And Mom had nothing to do
with Dad's death.

231
00:15:32,867 --> 00:15:39,833
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

232
00:15:41,867 --> 00:15:44,300
Our family won't be ruined
just because of this.

233
00:15:45,267 --> 00:15:47,800
We should protect each other.

234
00:15:48,933 --> 00:15:50,433
And we will do it

235
00:15:50,433 --> 00:15:52,067
for Dad.

236
00:15:55,933 --> 00:15:57,100
Jade.

237
00:15:57,100 --> 00:15:58,533
All I'm asking you

238
00:15:59,233 --> 00:16:03,000
is not to do anything
to hurt our family.

239
00:16:03,567 --> 00:16:05,933
And that includes Mom.

240
00:16:05,933 --> 00:16:12,867
[SOMBER MUSIC CONTINUES]

241
00:16:27,200 --> 00:16:29,000
Where did you get this video?

242
00:16:29,533 --> 00:16:31,433
That copy has
been requested before.

243
00:16:32,133 --> 00:16:34,100
But the owner of the car,
where the dashcam is,

244
00:16:34,100 --> 00:16:35,900
was out of the country.

245
00:16:35,900 --> 00:16:38,100
They just got back,
so we only got this today.

246
00:16:38,633 --> 00:16:40,567
Mrs. Almazan didn't include
in her statement

247
00:16:40,567 --> 00:16:42,833
that she was in the area
that day.

248
00:16:45,233 --> 00:16:47,067
This will greatly help our case.

249
00:16:50,167 --> 00:16:51,600
Still, circumstantial.

250
00:16:52,567 --> 00:16:53,600
You know that.

251
00:16:54,633 --> 00:16:57,400
But why didn't she tell us
about it before?

252
00:16:57,400 --> 00:17:04,367
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

253
00:17:12,500 --> 00:17:18,500
[MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]

254
00:17:18,533 --> 00:17:21,433
[INHALES DEEPLY, SIGHS LOUDLY]

255
00:17:23,300 --> 00:17:24,600
[BREATHES SHARPLY]

256
00:17:27,667 --> 00:17:29,500
[GLASS THUDS]

257
00:17:29,500 --> 00:17:30,500
[CLEARS THROAT]

258
00:17:31,533 --> 00:17:33,133
Ma'am.

259
00:17:33,133 --> 00:17:34,233
That's enough.

260
00:17:35,800 --> 00:17:37,133
[SIGHS DEEPLY]

261
00:17:43,633 --> 00:17:49,267
The kids already know
that I followed Fred.

262
00:17:52,400 --> 00:17:56,233
Would you like me to
tell them that I was with you?

263
00:17:56,233 --> 00:17:57,500
No, no.

264
00:17:59,167 --> 00:18:01,467
No need.

265
00:18:01,467 --> 00:18:03,400
[SIGHS]

266
00:18:03,400 --> 00:18:06,000
I already told them
everything.

267
00:18:07,400 --> 00:18:12,633
I'm just hoping that we'll patch
things up after this.

268
00:18:17,067 --> 00:18:18,333
I hope so too.

269
00:18:20,500 --> 00:18:22,033
Just remember, ma'am...

270
00:18:23,200 --> 00:18:27,200
You can tell me if there's
anything I can do to help.

271
00:18:29,600 --> 00:18:33,167
You know you have
my loyalty.

272
00:18:36,267 --> 00:18:39,200
I'm loyal to you... and sir.

273
00:18:40,600 --> 00:18:42,300
As well as your
whole family.

274
00:18:44,367 --> 00:18:49,133
Yes, I know that, and I
appreciate that, Roi.

275
00:18:50,400 --> 00:18:51,867
Thank you.

276
00:18:51,867 --> 00:18:54,733
[INHALES DEEPLY, SIGHS]

277
00:18:54,733 --> 00:18:57,700
You should go
and take a rest.

278
00:18:57,733 --> 00:19:04,533
[MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

279
00:19:04,533 --> 00:19:05,700
Okay, ma'am.

280
00:19:05,700 --> 00:19:06,733
[SIGHS DEEPLY]

281
00:19:06,733 --> 00:19:13,700
[MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

282
00:19:29,933 --> 00:19:33,433
[WAVES CRASHING]

283
00:19:33,433 --> 00:19:34,400
Dad.

284
00:19:35,833 --> 00:19:36,867
You're late.

285
00:19:39,767 --> 00:19:43,200
- I prepared that for you.
- Thanks, Dad.

286
00:19:45,300 --> 00:19:47,300
Isn't it still too early, Dad?

287
00:19:47,300 --> 00:19:51,267
Can't we just hang out
after lunch?

288
00:19:52,267 --> 00:19:53,233
[EDWARD GRUNTS]

289
00:19:53,900 --> 00:19:55,767
Son, you know in life,

290
00:19:55,767 --> 00:19:57,500
just like with
everything else,

291
00:19:57,500 --> 00:19:59,767
preparation is key.

292
00:19:59,767 --> 00:20:02,700
If you're not prepared,
you won't catch any fish.

293
00:20:03,600 --> 00:20:04,833
Got it, Dad.

294
00:20:05,767 --> 00:20:07,433
So, uh...

295
00:20:08,300 --> 00:20:12,433
Grace from reception mentioned
that Jade arrived at the resort.

296
00:20:13,767 --> 00:20:14,933
Yeah.

297
00:20:14,933 --> 00:20:18,733
Actually, they're asking for
help to promote Hotel 88.

298
00:20:20,200 --> 00:20:21,800
That's okay, right, Dad?

299
00:20:22,833 --> 00:20:24,233
Why not?

300
00:20:25,467 --> 00:20:29,233
Well, technically, they're
our competitor.

301
00:20:30,300 --> 00:20:32,533
We also have
a hotel and resort.

302
00:20:32,533 --> 00:20:35,467
- So...
- You know...

303
00:20:35,500 --> 00:20:37,300
I don't see it that way.

304
00:20:38,633 --> 00:20:40,633
Her parents are my friends.

305
00:20:42,333 --> 00:20:44,300
It's you I'm confused about.

306
00:20:47,000 --> 00:20:48,300
Why?

307
00:20:50,000 --> 00:20:51,467
You agreed to help?

308
00:20:53,367 --> 00:20:55,633
I mean, you cried back
in high school

309
00:20:55,633 --> 00:20:57,867
when Jade didn't show up
for prom.

310
00:20:58,967 --> 00:21:00,767
[SCOFFS]

311
00:21:01,533 --> 00:21:04,633
It's all in the past
and I've moved on from it.

312
00:21:04,633 --> 00:21:06,200
Or maybe...

313
00:21:07,200 --> 00:21:08,800
you agreed because
of Jade.

314
00:21:10,867 --> 00:21:11,867
Dad.

315
00:21:14,267 --> 00:21:17,500
You know what I see?

316
00:21:17,500 --> 00:21:21,567
It's that up to this day,
you're still hoping...

317
00:21:22,700 --> 00:21:24,667
that she'll like you.

318
00:21:24,667 --> 00:21:28,700
- [MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]
- [WAVES CRASHING]

319
00:21:28,700 --> 00:21:32,700
Dad, if she ends up
liking me,

320
00:21:32,700 --> 00:21:34,700
then that's her problem.

321
00:21:34,700 --> 00:21:37,800
As for me, I don't have plans
to get serious.

322
00:21:40,867 --> 00:21:42,667
[SIGHS DEEPLY]

323
00:21:42,700 --> 00:21:44,233
Son, you know...

324
00:21:45,433 --> 00:21:49,233
life is just like
the wide ocean.

325
00:21:54,367 --> 00:21:57,400
And we're all
just fishermen

326
00:21:57,400 --> 00:22:00,367
waiting for the right chances
to catch something good.

327
00:22:02,533 --> 00:22:06,533
If you just keep playing
around and don't get serious...

328
00:22:07,933 --> 00:22:09,867
you won't get
a good catch.

329
00:22:11,633 --> 00:22:14,867
You know, some fish
are worth keeping.

330
00:22:16,333 --> 00:22:17,433
Just saying.

331
00:22:19,000 --> 00:22:20,367
Come on, Dad.

332
00:22:21,600 --> 00:22:22,833
It's just Jade.

333
00:22:22,833 --> 00:22:28,100
[MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

334
00:22:28,100 --> 00:22:31,600
- Dad, Dad, Dad! I caught it!
- Okay. Pull.

335
00:22:34,733 --> 00:22:41,633
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

336
00:22:50,000 --> 00:22:53,767
What if Michael and Federico
didn't kill each other?

337
00:22:56,467 --> 00:22:59,433
Someone could've planted
the gun,

338
00:22:59,433 --> 00:23:01,000
- and fired it...
- [GUNSHOTS]

339
00:23:01,000 --> 00:23:03,500
...to make it look like
they killed each other.

340
00:23:07,467 --> 00:23:14,400
[UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]

341
00:23:16,000 --> 00:23:21,633
You mean they were
already dead

342
00:23:21,633 --> 00:23:23,500
when someone
planted the gun?

343
00:23:25,000 --> 00:23:27,500
There were no other
fingerprints found

344
00:23:27,500 --> 00:23:29,567
because the killer
is an expert.

345
00:23:29,567 --> 00:23:36,000
[UNSETTLING MUSIC CONTINUES]

346
00:23:36,000 --> 00:23:38,033
What if...

347
00:23:38,033 --> 00:23:41,467
Frida Almazan had really
something to do with this?

348
00:23:41,467 --> 00:23:48,433
[UNSETTLING MUSIC CONTINUES]

349
00:23:53,367 --> 00:23:54,267
I'm sure they've already talked
about that earring.

350
00:23:57,033 --> 00:24:03,633
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

351
00:24:03,733 --> 00:24:05,067
Okay.

352
00:24:05,200 --> 00:24:08,000
This is our official first day.

353
00:24:08,167 --> 00:24:09,400
But before anything,

354
00:24:10,400 --> 00:24:12,400
I know there's something
you want to ask us.

355
00:24:15,100 --> 00:24:16,300
The earring.

356
00:24:17,700 --> 00:24:18,867
As Jade said...

357
00:24:20,100 --> 00:24:21,300
it belongs to us.

358
00:24:22,033 --> 00:24:23,500
We won't deny it.

359
00:24:23,600 --> 00:24:25,167
Actually, we'd like to
apologize because...

360
00:24:25,267 --> 00:24:26,633
Because I lost it.

361
00:24:26,767 --> 00:24:31,800
[TENSE MUSIC RISES]

362
00:24:31,967 --> 00:24:33,333
The earring belongs to me.

363
00:24:49,300 --> 00:24:55,600
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES,
THEN FADES]

364
00:24:56,033 --> 00:24:57,700
<i>That family is really trying
to outsmart us.</i>

365
00:24:57,800 --> 00:24:59,100
<i>It's obvious that they're
covering up for someone.</i>

366
00:24:59,233 --> 00:25:00,567
<i>Just take care of
the hotel for now,</i>

367
00:25:00,700 --> 00:25:02,700
<i>and I'll find out the truth
from Jade.</i>

368
00:25:02,833 --> 00:25:03,867
<i>So, you're going
to use Jade?</i>

369
00:25:04,067 --> 00:25:06,433
<i>We can't keep
avoiding each other.</i>

370
00:25:06,500 --> 00:25:07,633
<i> Are you really that clueless?</i>

371
00:25:07,767 --> 00:25:10,733
<i>A lot has changed,
especially in our families.</i>

372
00:25:10,833 --> 00:25:12,233
<i>This case isn't over yet,
Marina.</i>

373
00:25:12,400 --> 00:25:14,233
<i>- I need solid evidence.
- [GRUNTING]</i>

374
00:25:14,433 --> 00:25:15,567
<i> We won't stop,</i>

375
00:25:15,667 --> 00:25:17,200
<i>especially if we know
something's wrong.</i>

376
00:25:17,300 --> 00:25:18,133
[THUDS]

377
00:25:18,300 --> 00:25:20,133
<i>Next time,
find someone else</i>

378
00:25:20,300 --> 00:25:21,933
<i>you can trick into
bailing you out!</i>

379
00:25:22,100 --> 00:25:24,100
<i> I've been waiting a long time!</i>

380
00:25:24,233 --> 00:25:26,400
<i> Until when will I be alone?</i>

381
00:25:26,500 --> 00:25:28,933
<i>If the hotel loses money,
it'll be your fault,</i>

382
00:25:29,067 --> 00:25:29,767
<i> and I'll charge you for it.</i>

383
00:25:29,967 --> 00:25:31,400
<i>I can push through
with this event.</i>

384
00:25:31,467 --> 00:25:32,767
<i> Can you?</i>

385
00:25:35,833 --> 00:25:36,733
<i> I can.</i>

